&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Acetic acid&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 21px; font-weight: bolder; font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Industrially, acetic acid is primarily produced by the &lt;strong&gt;carbonylation of methanol&lt;/strong&gt;, which involves the reaction of methanol with carbon monoxide in the presence of a catalyst.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The process is widely known as the &lt;strong&gt;Monsanto process&lt;/strong&gt; or the &lt;strong&gt;Cativa process&lt;/strong&gt;, utilizing rhodium or iridium-based catalysts for high efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This method is preferred due to its high yield and cost-effectiveness compared to other production methods.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Acetic acid is a &lt;strong&gt;key ingredient in the production of synthetic fibers, plastics, and other chemical compounds&lt;/strong&gt;, such as vinyl acetate and acetic anhydride.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Globally, acetic acid is extensively used in industries ranging from food to pharmaceuticals and is a vital commodity chemical.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nitric acid&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Nitric acid is a highly corrosive mineral acid primarily used in the production of fertilizers, explosives, and nitration reactions.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is industrially produced by the &lt;strong&gt;Ostwald process&lt;/strong&gt;, which involves the catalytic oxidation of ammonia.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Nitric acid is not synthesized by the carbonylation of methanol.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Citric acid&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Citric acid is an organic acid naturally found in citrus fruits and is widely used as a food additive and preservative.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is produced industrially via the &lt;strong&gt;fermentation of carbohydrates&lt;/strong&gt;, such as molasses or glucose, using Aspergillus niger fungus.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is unrelated to the carbonylation of methanol process.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hydrochloric acid&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Hydrochloric acid is a strong acid formed by dissolving hydrogen chloride gas in water.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is primarily used in metal cleaning, pH regulation, and chemical synthesis.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Hydrochloric acid is not produced through the carbonylation of methanol.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Aids Digestion&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dietary fibre&lt;/strong&gt;, also known as roughage or bulk, is primarily found in plant-based foods such as fruits, vegetables, whole grains, nuts, and seeds.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is a type of carbohydrate that is not digestible by human enzymes, meaning it passes through the digestive system relatively intact.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;One of the primary functions of dietary fibre is to &lt;strong&gt;aid digestion&lt;/strong&gt; by adding bulk to the stool, which helps prevent constipation and promotes regular bowel movements.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Dietary fibre can help maintain a healthy gut microbiome by serving as food for beneficial gut bacteria, which produce short-chain fatty acids that contribute to gut health.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Soluble fibre can help regulate blood sugar levels and lower cholesterol by slowing the absorption of sugar and binding to cholesterol in the digestive tract, though these benefits are secondary to its primary role in digestion.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It does not provide energy directly, as it is not broken down into glucose, nor does it contribute to muscle building or increase cholesterol levels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Types of Dietary Fibre:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Soluble fibre:&lt;/strong&gt; Found in foods like oats, barley, and fruits such as apples and citrus. It dissolves in water and forms a gel-like substance that can help lower cholesterol and stabilize blood sugar levels.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Insoluble fibre:&lt;/strong&gt; Found in foods like whole grains, nuts, seeds, and vegetables. It does not dissolve in water and primarily adds bulk to stool, aiding in regular bowel movements and preventing constipation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Health Benefits:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Consuming adequate dietary fibre can help prevent several digestive disorders such as &lt;strong&gt;diverticular disease&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;irritable bowel syndrome&lt;/strong&gt; (IBS), and &lt;strong&gt;constipation&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Dietary fibre is associated with a lower risk of chronic diseases such as &lt;strong&gt;type 2 diabetes&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;heart disease&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;certain types of cancer&lt;/strong&gt;, particularly colorectal cancer.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It can contribute to weight management by promoting a feeling of fullness, thereby reducing overall calorie intake.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Recommended Intake:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;World Health Organization (WHO)&lt;/strong&gt; recommends adults consume at least &lt;strong&gt;25-30 grams&lt;/strong&gt; of dietary fibre daily from a variety of food sources.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Children and adolescents require slightly less depending on their age, ranging from &lt;strong&gt;15-25 grams per day&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Examples of High-Fibre Foods:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Whole grains like &lt;strong&gt;brown rice&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;quinoa&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;whole wheat bread&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Legumes such as &lt;strong&gt;lentils&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;chickpeas&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;black beans&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Fruits such as &lt;strong&gt;bananas&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;apples&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;berries&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Vegetables like &lt;strong&gt;broccoli&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;carrots&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;spinach&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Nuts and seeds such as &lt;strong&gt;almonds&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;chia seeds&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;flaxseeds&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Misconceptions about Dietary Fibre:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Dietary fibre does not directly provide &lt;strong&gt;energy&lt;/strong&gt; or &lt;strong&gt;calories&lt;/strong&gt; because it is not digestible.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It does not help build &lt;strong&gt;muscle&lt;/strong&gt;, as its function is primarily related to digestion and gut health.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;While dietary fibre can lower &lt;strong&gt;cholesterol&lt;/strong&gt;, it does not increase it.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Global Trends:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Many regions, including &lt;strong&gt;North America&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;Europe&lt;/strong&gt;, report a significant fibre deficiency in their diets, often due to the prevalence of processed foods.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Countries such as &lt;strong&gt;India&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;China&lt;/strong&gt;, with diets rich in grains, legumes, and vegetables, typically meet or exceed recommended fibre levels.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Practical Tips for Increasing Fibre Intake:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Replace refined grains with &lt;strong&gt;whole grains&lt;/strong&gt;, such as switching from white bread to whole wheat bread.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Add more &lt;strong&gt;fruits&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;vegetables&lt;/strong&gt; to meals and snacks.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Incorporate &lt;strong&gt;nuts&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;seeds&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;legumes&lt;/strong&gt; into daily meals.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Hydrate adequately, as fibre requires water to move effectively through the digestive system.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;f = 1/T&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 21px; font-weight: bolder; font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The frequency (&lt;strong&gt;f&lt;/strong&gt;) of a sound wave is inversely proportional to its time period (&lt;strong&gt;T&lt;/strong&gt;), expressed as &lt;strong&gt;f = 1/T&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Frequency&lt;/strong&gt; refers to the number of oscillations or cycles a wave completes per second, measured in Hertz (&lt;strong&gt;Hz&lt;/strong&gt;).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Time period (T)&lt;/strong&gt; is the time taken by one complete wave cycle, typically measured in seconds (&lt;strong&gt;s&lt;/strong&gt;).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A higher frequency corresponds to a shorter time period, indicating that the wave oscillates faster.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This relationship is fundamental to understanding wave dynamics in physics and acoustics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Wave Frequency:&lt;/strong&gt; It is the reciprocal of the time period, signifying the rate of repetition of the wave motion. Mathematically, &lt;strong&gt;f = 1/T&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hertz (Hz):&lt;/strong&gt; The unit of frequency, where 1 Hz equals one cycle per second.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Time Period:&lt;/strong&gt; Represented as &lt;strong&gt;T&lt;/strong&gt;, it is calculated as the time required for one complete oscillation or wave cycle.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Wave Motion:&lt;/strong&gt; It is a periodic disturbance that propagates through a medium, transferring energy without transporting matter.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Applications:&lt;/strong&gt; Understanding frequency and time period is crucial in various fields like acoustics, communication systems, and musical instruments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pitchblende&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 21px; font-weight: bolder; font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Neptunium and plutonium are radioactive elements that belong to the actinide series in the periodic table.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Pitchblende, also known as uraninite, is a naturally occurring mineral that primarily contains uranium oxides and is the primary source of these elements.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Neptunium and plutonium are found as trace elements in pitchblende due to the decay and nuclear processes involving uranium isotopes.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Pitchblende is mined in regions with uranium deposits, such as Canada, the United States, and parts of Africa.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The discovery of neptunium and plutonium was closely tied to research on uranium and its decay products, which are often extracted from pitchblende for scientific and industrial purposes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pitchblende:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is a mineral that contains uranium as its primary constituent and traces of thorium, radium, and other radioactive elements.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Pitchblende is black and has a high density, making it a significant source for extracting uranium and its decay products.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Neptunium:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is a transuranic element with the atomic number 93 and symbol Np.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Neptunium is formed as a byproduct in nuclear reactors or from uranium-238 undergoing neutron capture.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Plutonium:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is a transuranic element with the atomic number 94 and symbol Pu.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Plutonium is used as a fuel in nuclear reactors and as a key component in nuclear weapons.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Actinide Series:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The actinide series consists of 15 elements, from actinium to lawrencium, characterized by their radioactive nature.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;These elements are typically found in minerals like pitchblende and monazite sand.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Radioactive Decay:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is the process by which unstable atomic nuclei lose energy by emitting radiation.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Uranium in pitchblende undergoes radioactive decay to produce elements like radium, polonium, neptunium, and plutonium.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;It initiated a new scientific domain&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Human Genome Project&lt;/strong&gt; was completed in &lt;strong&gt;2003&lt;/strong&gt;, marking a milestone in understanding human genetics.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It involved sequencing the entire human genome, which comprises approximately &lt;strong&gt;3 billion base pairs&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The initiative laid the foundation for a new scientific domain known as &lt;strong&gt;genomics&lt;/strong&gt;, which integrates genetic information with biological functions.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The sequencing revolutionized fields such as &lt;strong&gt;personalized medicine&lt;/strong&gt;, enabling treatments tailored to individual genetic profiles.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Advancements in genome sequencing have facilitated the study of genetic disorders and susceptibility to diseases like &lt;strong&gt;cancer, diabetes, and cardiovascular conditions&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It catalyzed the development of bioinformatics, combining computational tools to analyze vast genetic datasets.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The project also opened pathways for &lt;strong&gt;gene editing technologies&lt;/strong&gt;, such as &lt;strong&gt;CRISPR-Cas9&lt;/strong&gt;, enabling precise modifications in genetic material.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Beyond medicine, genome sequencing impacts agriculture, for example, by enhancing crop yield and resistance through genetic studies.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Human Genome Project marked a pivotal shift in scientific research, fostering interdisciplinary approaches across &lt;strong&gt;biology, chemistry, computer science, and engineering&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
